question: Emily has 10 jars of frosting in her storage room. Each jar of frosting can decorate 14 muffins. Emily wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her frosting. If each pan holds 10 muffins, how many pans worth of muffins should she bake?
answer:
She has enough frosting for 10 * 14 = <<10*14=140>>140 muffins.
She needs 140 / 10 = <<140/10=14>>14 pans to bake all of the muffins.
#### 14
